# Caddy gives your relay automatic HTTPS (and the wss:// upgrade) with zero config.
# 1. Point relay.yourtown.org's DNS A record at your server's IP.
# 2. Put this next to your docker-compose, run Caddy (or add it as a service).
# 3. Your relay is live at wss://relay.yourtown.org
#
# Replace the domain with yours. Caddy fetches and renews the TLS cert automatically.
relay.yourtown.org {
	reverse_proxy 127.0.0.1:8080
}
